This paper discusses the evolution and detection of malwares, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the challenges faced by anti-malware developers due to the creation of variants by second generation malwares, which can be addressed by using techniques such as machine learning (cs.AI) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper discusses the need for continuous updates and improvements in anti-malware systems, which can be related to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper also mentions the impact of malwares on infrastructure, which can be related to systems and network security (cs.SI).
